text: Hainburg an der Donau is a town in Bruck an der Leitha district in Lower Austria, east of Vienna. In 2022, 6,892 people lived there. Its town walls are some of the oldest and best-preserved in Europe. Actually, the name of the city is only Hainburg, the part after it stands for the river Danube, which flows past Hainburg an der Donau. == References == == Other websites == * Category:Settlements in Lower Austria
title: Hainburg an der Donau
